f3: **\@inbook** is a [book]{.underline} with [section]{.underline} or [start/end]{.underline} (reference to page number or range).
In **BibTeX** it may be the address of a **publisher, conference, organization, institution** or **school**.
This is a special key in [CFF]{.underline} resembling the **BibteX** entry.
If [section]{.underline} or [start-end]{.underline} informed, it would be treated as **\@inbook**
Use also [thesis-type]{.underline} for identifying the thesis type.

f2: A work of art, e.g., a painting
An edited work, e.g., a book
A historical work, e.g., a medieval manuscript
A music file or sheet music
Slides, i.e., a published slide deck
A software container (e.g., a docker container)
An executable software, i.e., a binary/artifact
